AIM:
To create a database trigger that automatically logs every INSERT or UPDATE operation performed on a table, and to create a VIEW that displays daily activity reports. 
This demonstrates how automated auditing is implemented in enterprise systems.

PROCEDURE:
Create a main table (employees) where data changes will occur.
Create a log table (activity_log) to store audit details.
Write a trigger that fires automatically on every:
INSERT
UPDATE
Insert and update data to test the trigger.
Create a VIEW to generate a daily summary of activity.
Retrieve the view to display daily audit reports.

code:
Creating Tables

CREATE TABLE employees (
    emp_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    emp_name VARCHAR(100),
    salary DECIMAL(10,2),
    updated_on TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE activity_log (
    log_id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    emp_id INT,
    action_type VARCHAR(20),
    old_salary DECIMAL(10,2),
    new_salary DECIMAL(10,2),
    log_time TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TRIGGER log_insert
AFTER INSERT ON employees
FOR EACH ROW
INSERT INTO activity_log(emp_id, action_type, new_salary)
VALUES (NEW.emp_id, 'INSERT', NEW.salary);

CREATE TRIGGER log_update
AFTER UPDATE ON employees
FOR EACH ROW
INSERT INTO activity_log(emp_id, action_type, old_salary, new_salary)
VALUES (OLD.emp_id, 'UPDATE', OLD.salary, NEW.salary);

Inserting and Updating values 

INSERT INTO employees VALUES (1, 'Jeeva', 30000, NOW());

UPDATE employees
SET salary = 35000
WHERE emp_id = 1;

Creating Daily Activity Table

CREATE VIEW daily_activity AS
SELECT 
    DATE(log_time) AS activity_date,
    COUNT(*) AS total_actions,
    SUM(CASE WHEN action_type='INSERT' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS total_inserts,
    SUM(CASE WHEN action_type='UPDATE' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS total_updates
FROM activity_log
GROUP BY DATE(log_time);

See the Daily Report

SELECT * FROM daily_activity;

RESULT:
Thus, automated logging was successfully implemented using SQL Triggers that recorded every INSERT and UPDATE action performed on the employees table. 
A VIEW was created to summarize daily database activities, enabling easy audit tracking and reporting. This simulates real-time enterprise auditing systems used in banking, HR, and large-scale applications.
